headline: POOL Q3 Deep Dive: Margin Expansion and Technology Investment Amid Cautious Consumer Demand
summary: Swimming pool distributor Pool (NASDAQ:POOL) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 1.3% year on year to $1.45 billion. Its GAAP profit of $3.40 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Pool Corp (POOL) Margin Declines Challenge Bullish Narratives Despite High-Quality Earnings
summary: Pool (POOL) posted a net profit margin of 7.7%, down from 8.5% a year ago, and has faced a 2.8% annual decline in earnings over the past five years, with negative earnings growth in the most recent year. Looking ahead, analysts expect earnings to increase 6.5% per year and revenue to grow at 4% annually. Both figures lag broader US market averages.
